         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">BIOLOGICAL STATION, ¶ WATSON'S BAY. ¶ Sydney, N.S.W. 28 August 1885. ¶ In the greatest haste ¶ Highly esteemed Baron,...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">85.08.28a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">From Nikolai Miklouho-Maclay</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M1, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS found with <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Musa maclayi</seg> (MEL 588788). MS annotation by M: 'Beantw. 2/9/85' [Answered 2/9/85].</p>
               </note>
               <seg rend="form%20text"
                    style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, 'Times New Roman'; ">BIOLOGICAL STATION,</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="form%20text"
                    style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, 'Times New Roman'; ">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>WATSON'S BAY.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="form%20text"
                    style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, 'Times New Roman'; ">
                  <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Sydney, N.S.W.</seg>
               </seg> 28 August <seg rend="form%20text"
                    style="color: #2f5496; font-family: Times, 'Times New Roman'; ">
                  <seg style="font-style: italic; ">188</seg>
               </seg>5.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">In grösster Eile</hi>
               </seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This has been written diagonally across the top left-hand corner of the page.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">Hochgeehrter Herr Baron,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich werde die Freiheit haben und Ihnen die “</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Correctur”</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> meiner Liste zuschicken, </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">mit der </hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Bitte</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">: einige Zusätze (falls Sie Zeit dazu finden!) nicht zu versagen! z.B. Ich möchte wissen, welcher Reisende</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline"> vor</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> mir (i.e. </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">vor</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> 1871) den </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Piper%20methysticum">Piper methysticum</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">von New Guinea</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> mitgebracht hat? (Unter den Papuan Plants (pag. 98 Ihres Werkes über dieselben wird der Name P. meth. mit anzogen</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>angezogen?</p>
               </note>
               <seg style="">).</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jede Zeile </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">von Ihnen</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> wird den wissenschaftlichen Werth meiner kleinen </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ethnologischen</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Notiz vermehren. Auch würde es jedenfalls äusserste interessant sein, Ihre Ansicht über die </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">wilden</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Bananen Arten N. Guinea's sowie den wilden Sacharum offic. zu erfahren!</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="frame"/>
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Einige Skizzen und die enormen</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The small sketch included here is in the left-hand margin of the letter and has an arrow linking it to 'enormen' in the text: 85-08-28a_image01.jpg</p>
               </note>
               <seg style=""> Bananen Samen werde ich am Montag Ihnen zusenden, sowie die Correctur, sobald der Aufsatz gedruckt ist.</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">freundschaftlich grüssend</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Hochachtungsvoll</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>N. de M. Maclay</seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">BIOLOGICAL STATION,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">WATSON'S BAY.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Sydney, N.S.W. 28 August 1885.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">In the greatest haste</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Highly esteemed Baron,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will take the liberty and send you the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">proof</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>of my list <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">with the</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">request</hi>
               </seg> not to refuse some additions (if you find the time for it)! e.g. I would like to know, which explorer <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">before</hi>
               </seg> me (i.e. <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">before</hi>
               </seg> 1871) has brought back <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Piper%20methysticum">Piper methysticum</name>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">from New Guinea</hi>
               </seg>? (The name <seg style="font-style: italic; ">P. meth</seg>. is cited among the Papuan Plants page 98 of your work about them).<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B77.13.02.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Any line <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">from you</hi>
               </seg> will increase the scientific value of my small <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ethnological</hi>
               </seg> note. In any case it would also be highly interesting to ascertain your opinion about the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">wild</hi>
               </seg> banana species of New Guinea as well as the wild <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Sacharum offic</seg>.<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Saccharum officinarum</seg>?</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note type="frame"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I will send you some sketches and the enormous<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <seg style="">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     </seg>The small sketch included here is in the left-hand margin of the letter and has an arrow linking it to 'enormen' in the text: 85-08-28a_image01.jpg</p>
               </note> banana seeds on Monday,<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See N. Miklouho-Maclay to M, 29 August 1885 (in this edition as 85-08-29a).</p>
               </note> as well as the proof, as soon as the article is printed.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">friendly greetings</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>respectfully</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>N. de M. Maclay.<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A small newspaper cutting is affixed to the MS and headed in Miklouho-Maclay's writing, with some underlining as shown probably also by him: '<seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">At the meeting of Lin. Soc. of N.S.W. on the 26th Aug</hi>
                     </seg>.'. It lists the first paper read at the meeting: </p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">List of plants in use by the natives of the Maclay Coast, New Guinea</hi>
                     </seg>. By N. de Miklouho-Maclay, with botanical remarks by Baron Ferd. von Mueller, K.C.M.G., &amp;c. Baron Maclay in this paper gives — (1), a list of the plants used as food, dividing them into those cultivated and those growing wild; (2), those cultivated <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">as stimulants</hi>
                     </seg>, or <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">for medicine</hi>
                     </seg>; (3), those <seg style="">
                        <hi rend="underline">useful in various ways for household purposes</hi>
                     </seg>; and (4), those introduced since 1871. An appendix, by Baron Mueller, gives an account of some of the plants mentioned by Baron Maclay, and gives a description of a new species named Bassia Maclayana.'.</p>
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M described the species in B85.04.01.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Piper%20methysticum">Piper methysticum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Sacharum%20officinarum">Sacharum officinarum</name>
            </p>
